20school%20took%20me%20to%20Kuwait.%20That's%20where%20I%20met%20my%20husband%2C%20Ziad%2C%20who%20is%20from%20Saudi%20Arabia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZiad%20and%20I%20worked%20together%2C%20and%20we%20were%20as%20dedicated%20to%20our%20company%20as%20we%20were%20to%20each%20other.%20The%20company%20put%20us%20on%20a%20dual%20career%20track%2C%20meaning%20we'd%20be%20working%20from%20the%20same%20location.%20Then%2C%20they%20transferred%20us%20to%20Angola%2C%20in%20West%20Africa.%20Three%20years%20after%20Zaid%20and%20I%20met%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcouple-met-on-flight-ditched-destination-wedding-elope-paris-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewe%20got%20engaged%20in%20Paris%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20a%20vacation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrides-see-through-lace-gown-fit-perfectly-with-forest-wedding-2020-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EWe%20planned%20a%20wedding%20in%20Africa%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20got%20married%20in%20New%20Jersey.%20But%20once%20we%20were%20ready%20to%20start%20a%20family%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20leave%20Africa%20so%20I%20wouldn't%20need%20to%20worry%20about%20diseases%20like%20malaria%20while%20pregnant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20asked%20our%20company%20to%20transfer%20us%20again%2C%20and%20now%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmove-to-svalbard-norway-what-life-will-be-like-2020-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewe%20live%20in%20Norway%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20our%20two%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220d4ca9e1-d923-44d7-aafb-ac47e039cf4f%5C%22%3EThe%20nature%20around%20our%20home%20is%20beautiful%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EZiad%2C%20who%20grew%20up%20in%20the%20desert%2C%20said%20he%20wanted%20to%20live%20somewhere%20he%20could%20see%20the%20ocean%2C%20mountains%2C%20and%20snow.%20I%20told%20him%20I%20didn't%20think%20that%20place%20existed%2C%20but%20I%20was%20wrong.%20Our%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fliving-most-northern-town-on-earth-longyearbyen-norway-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etransferred%20us%20to%20Norway%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20we%20immediately%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20we%20live%20about%2020%20minutes%20(by%20ferry%20and%20bus)%20outside%20Norway's%20second-largest%20city.%20I%20can%20see%20fjords%20and%20mountains%20from%20our%20living%20room.%20We're%20on%20an%20island%20with%20hiking%20trails%20all%20around.%20Our%20house%20is%20comparable%20to%20an%20American%20home%3A%205%20bedrooms%2C%203%20bathrooms%2C%20and%20a%20huge%20yard%20with%20plum%20trees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dd31e3c6-b421-43b4-a290-b2486cf9a20e%5C%22%3EParental%20leave%20is%20mandatory%20for%20men%20and%20women%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELiving%20here%2C%20I%20understand%20why%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhappiest-country-best-place-to-live-2017-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENorway%20is%20one%20of%20the%20happiest%20countries%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20world%2C%20especially%20for%20parents.%20It%20starts%20with%20parental%20leave%2C%20which%20is%20mandatory%20for%20both%20mothers%20and%20fathers.%20I%20had%20about%20nine%20months%20of%20paid%20leave%2C%20and%20Zaid%20had%20about%20four%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Monica%20Virga%20Alborno%20with%20baby%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68388358ca50259add4d4a3f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMonica%20Virga%20Alborno%20had%20nine%20months%20of%20paid%20maternity%20leave%20in%20Norway.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Monica%20Virga%20Alborno%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EParental%20leave%20isn't%20meant%20to%20run%20concurrently%20but%20to%20flow%20one%20after%20the%20other.%20When%20the%20mother%20returns%20to%20work%2C%20the%20father%20picks%20up%20the%20home%20duties.%20From%20the%20beginning%2C%20both%20parents%20are%20responsible%20for%20the%20home%20and%20the%20baby.%20This%20policy%20results%20in%20more%20moms%20returning%20to%20work%20and%20a%20better%20balance%20in%20the%20household%2C%20I%20think.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2279f8240d-c273-4942-86ce-8b963900c9ea%5C%22%3EThe%20public%20day%20care%20is%20an%20affordable%20forest%20school%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20my%20kids%20attend%20Barnehage%2C%20a%20Norwegian%20public%20day%20care%20that's%20a%20cross%20between%20forest%20school%20and%20Montessori%20education.%20Because%20of%20Barnehage%2C%20both%20my%20kids%20speak%20Norwegian%20%E2%80%94%20which%20I'm%20still%20struggling%20to%20pick%20up.%20They%20learn%20to%20get%20outside%20in%20all%20weather%20and%20bake%20homemade%20bread.%20Truly%2C%20I%20couldn't%20design%20a%20better%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cost%20for%20both%20kids%20to%20attend%20for%2040%20hours%20a%20week%20is%20%24420%20total.%20I%20also%20receive%20a%20monthly%20stipend%20for%20the%20kids%2C%20which%20will%20continue%20until%20they're%20about%2016.%20That%20amounts%20to%20%24350%20monthly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f34c2e55-364e-42a6-aa40-e9fe584a41be%5C%22%3EA%20pelvic%20floor%20therapist%20visited%20the%20day%20after%20I%20gave%20birth%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMedical%20care%20in%20Norway%20is%20high-quality%2C%20but%20it%20has%20a%20more%20holistic%20approach%2C%20especially%20during%20pregnancy.%20During%20both%20pregnancies%2C%20I%20wasn't%20seen%20until%2012%20weeks.%20Pregnancy%20and%20birth%20were%20treated%20like%20natural%20processes%2C%20not%20medical%20events.%20The%20maternity%20floor%20had%20dim%20lighting%2C%20and%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20the%20staff%20left%20me%20alone%20unless%20they%20were%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20needed%20an%20emergency%20C-section%20with%20my%20daughter%2C%20the%20care%20was%20outstanding.%20A%20pelvic%20floor%20specialist%20even%20visited%20me%20in%20recovery%20so%20I%20could%20start%20healing%20my%20core%20on%20day%20one.%20I%20wanted%20to%20try%20for%20a%20VBAC%20with%20my%20son%2C%20and%20I%20met%20with%20a%20team%20at%20the%20hospital%20who%20explained%20how%20I%20could%20safely%20do%20that%20(which%20I%20did).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226d9918e0-c1d9-430c-a439-9191b468cdaa%5C%22%3EThe%20quality%20of%20care%20makes%20me%20OK%20with%20higher%20taxes%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20my%20daughter%20had%20a%20severe%20virus%20that%20left%20her%20intubated%20in%20the%20ICU%20for%20nearly%20a%20week.%20She%20had%20two%20nurses%20assigned%20to%20her%2024%2F7%2C%20and%20a%20massage%20therapist%20who%20came%20in%20frequently.%20They%20even%20kept%20a%20diary%20of%20what%20happened%20to%20her%20each%20day%2C%20including%20pictures.%20They%20explained%20this%20helps%20patients%20understand%20the%20time%20they%20lose%20when%20they're%20unconscious.%20My%20daughter%20only%20has%20positive%20memories%2C%20despite%20the%20traumatic%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20she%20was%20transferred%20to%20the%20children's%20hospital%2C%20there%20were%20literally%20bicycling%20clowns%20to%20entertain%20the%20kids.%20Americans%20are%20quick%20to%20point%20out%20Norway%20has%20higher%20taxes%2C%20and%20that's%20true%20%E2%80%94%20I%20pay%20up%20to%2038%25%20of%20my%20income%20in%20tax.%20And%20yet%2C%20I%20can%20see%20the%20direct%20benefit%20of%20my%20tax%20money%20on%20my%20quality%20of%20life%20and%20the%20care%20my%20children%20receive%2C%20so%20it%20doesn't%20bother%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-raising-kids-in-norway-differences-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1752331921000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F683883186ffb6822ec61bb44%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-raising-kids-in-norway-differences-2025-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Monica%20Virga%20Alborno%20moved%20to%20Norway%